author: ALEX GROVES
title: MURRIETA: Police arrest two on drug-related counts
text:
By ALEX GROVES / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 8, 2015 Updated: 4:04 p.m. MURRIETA: Police arrest two on drug-related counts Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» Murrieta police officers arrested two people on drug- and theft-related counts when they pulled them over for a traffic stop, authorities said.
Annaliza Jocson and Jose Antonio Gomez, both 31, were arrested and booked at Southwest Detention Center on Wednesday, Oct. 7.
Jocson was arrested on suspicion of possessing methamphetamine to sell it and violation of her probation. She remained in custody Wednesday afternoon in lieu of $30,000, online jail records show.
Gomez was arrested on suspicion of possessing methamphetamine to sell it as well as possession of stolen property. He remained in custody Wednesday afternoon in lieu of $100,000, online jail records show.
Police officers stopped Jocson and Gomez in the area of Via Princesa and Murrieta Hot Springs Road about 3:10 a.m. They found that both were in possession of methamphetamine, according to a Murrieta police news release.
Jocson had an outstanding warrant for her arrest and Gomez was in possession of passports that police determined were taken during burglaries in Hemet and Riverside, according to the release.
